{
  "text": "T , isolated from a pool of leaves collected from Galium album at the Environmental Monitoring and Climate Impact Research Station Linden of the Justus-Liebig University Giessen (50 32¢ N 8 41.3¢ E) in Linden-Leihgestern near Giessen, Germany. The original colony was pale pink pigmented and had a diameter of 5.0 mm. Isolation and long-term maintenance of the strain were performed as described in detail previously [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
